{"unit": "fab-the-hooded-hand-21", "kind": "prose", "entity": "Tyland Lannister", "slug": "tyland-lannister", "text": "He claimed to have forgotten who was black or green and served the son of the queen who had tortured him", "line": 87, "hedge_term": "mushroom", "hedge_distance": 0}
{"unit": "fab-the-hooded-hand-21", "kind": "prose", "entity": "Tyland Lannister", "slug": "tyland-lannister", "text": "He came to dominate Leowyn Corbray and gathered power as the regents met less often", "line": 87, "hedge_term": "mushroom", "hedge_distance": 0}
{"unit": "fab-the-hooded-hand-21", "kind": "prose", "entity": "Baela Targaryen", "slug": "baela-targaryen", "text": "She took part in horse races, moonlight swims, and gathered unsuitable companions", "line": 207, "hedge_term": "eustace", "hedge_distance": 0}
{"unit": "fab-the-hooded-hand-21", "kind": "prose", "entity": "Baela Targaryen", "slug": "baela-targaryen", "text": "According to Baela's own provocation, she had bedded two of Rowan's sons, though Gyldayn notes the truth of it cannot be said", "line": 223, "hedge_term": "purportedly", "hedge_distance": 0}
{"unit": "fab-the-hooded-hand-21", "kind": "prose", "entity": "Alicent Hightower", "slug": "alicent-hightower", "text": "She died of Winter Fever the same night as Lord Westerling", "line": 319, "hedge_term": "avers", "hedge_distance": 0}
{"unit": "fab-the-hooded-hand-21", "kind": "prose", "entity": "Alyn Velaryon", "slug": "alyn-velaryon", "text": "He rewarded the reconciled claimants Daemion and Daeron with lands for ships", "line": 167, "hedge_term": "mushroom", "hedge_distance": 0}
{"unit": "fab-the-hooded-hand-21", "kind": "prose", "entity": "Orwyle", "slug": "orwyle", "text": "Tyland, an old green-council comrade, spared him and confined him to a comfortable cell, where he wrote confessions that fed Munkun's True Telling", "line": 151, "hedge_term": "mushroom", "hedge_distance": 0}
{"unit": "fab-the-hooded-hand-21", "kind": "prose", "entity": "Cregan Stark", "slug": "cregan-stark", "text": "He was offered a place among the regents but refused", "line": 63, "hedge_term": "eustace", "hedge_distance": 0}
{"unit": "fab-the-hooded-hand-21", "kind": "prose", "entity": "Alysanne Blackwood", "slug": "alysanne-blackwood", "text": "Her matchmaking was largely a great success, strengthening the riverlords and spreading worship of the old gods", "line": 23, "hedge_term": "mushroom", "hedge_distance": 0}
{"unit": "fab-the-hooded-hand-21", "kind": "prose", "entity": "Johanna Lannister", "slug": "johanna-lannister", "text": "She appealed repeatedly to the Hand, her late husband's twin, for aid", "line": 267, "hedge_term": "avers", "hedge_distance": 0}
{"unit": "fab-the-hooded-hand-21", "kind": "prose", "entity": "Johanna Lannister", "slug": "johanna-lannister", "text": "Donning a man's mail, she led the westermen to rout the raiders and save Kayce, though the songs of her slaying a dozen ironmen are dismissed", "line": 267, "hedge_term": "avers", "hedge_distance": 0}
